    "body": "A nit in the instructions to upgrade Ruby is that they say\n\n> you can use RVM to use Ruby 2.x for testing without upgrading the version of Ruby on your whole system\n\nleaving one googling for instructions to upgrade the version on the whole system (no temporary testing). ~~Turns out RVM just works as well, but the time being confused was already spent :)~~\n~~Actually, I'm not sure RVM works for that (at least as instructed), because after following those instructions I suddenly don't have Cocoapods installed anymore?~~\nYeah previously-installed gems (like Cocoapods) aren't part of the local environment, and discovering how to install one isn't straightforward (`sudo gem install` will succeed but doesn't work, Google says `rvm gem install`, which errors out suggesting `gem install` instead, which works).\n"
